--- PART 2: Signed Pfaffian — does sign matter? ---

The Pfaffian has a SIGN (±). Does the sign carry information?
Note: Pf(S) depends on the labeling of vertices.
Under permutation σ: Pf(P^T S P) = sign(σ) · Pf(S)
So the sign is labeling-dependent, but |Pf| is an invariant.

n = 4: signs observed
  H=  1 |Pf|=  1 signs={1}
  H=  3 |Pf|=  3 signs={1, -1}
  H=  5 |Pf|=  1 signs={-1}

